dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Udawatte st †Ramdin b Gayle 73 (121b 5x4 1x6) SR: 60.33

dismissalComment.html: Fab work from Ramdin. It was fired in quick, outside leg, Udawatte missed his sweep and Ramdin gathered it and quickly took the bails off as Udawatte dragged his feet outside the crease. Udawatte falls after making 73. Ramdin has had a great day behind the stumps. A very good catch down the leg side and now this.

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Powell b Bravo 17 (25b 1x4 1x6) SR: 68

dismissalComment.html: What a catch by Powell at short fine-leg! Fabulicious! Mahela had shuffled across to the off stump and pulled a short-of-length delivery to the leg side. Powell jumped, with his right hand stretched out, and it popped up off his palm and looked like it would fall to the ground behind him but he quickly swivelled around and lunged to take the rebound.

dismissalText.commentary: Thilan Thushara run out (Taylor) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Chaotic end! Two direct hits! The batsman missed a full delivery but ran for the bye. Ramdin's throw missed the stumps, Taylor picked it up, turned around and broke  the stumps at the non-striker's end. They run for the rebound. Another direct hit, from Ramdin, comes at the striker's end. Taufel takes the safe route and goes to the third umpire who rules that Taylor's throw had caught the batsman short. Phew!. So no run off the final ball.

commentTextItems.html: full in length, angling across, steered to the backward point region.

commentPostTextItems.html: 9.38 pm The game has been abandoned. West Indies have won the series 2-0. Pity, it had to end like this but that's that. Thanks for joining us. Good bye and good luck.

9:15 pm Raining again. The covers are back on. It's pouring down. Things are looking gloomy. Would it stop soon and will they have time to mop the ground dry? Tricky situation here. It's still raining.
8:57 pm: The umpires will inspect the conditions in a short while again.
8:48 pm The match referee walks out with Simon Taufel. There is still some concern over the wet outfield. So the drying process continues.

8.43 pm It's stopped raining a short while back. The umpires have been out there, checking the state of the outfield. No official word yet, on the start time. The umpires are working out the D/L targets. Once they finish that, they will start the game.

8:05 pm Rain suspends play. Cozier informs that the breeze is blowing pretty hard and it might just be a passing shower. No play for the moment, though. The wind is indeed pretty strong. Meanwhile, the rain gets heavier.

commentPreTextItems.html: Drizzling again. The ground staff are getting ready with the covers

commentPostTextItems.html: Ram from Canada: "Well it looks like West Indies finally have an opening batsman. The thing is that just a couple of years ago a guy by the name of Shiv used to open the ODIs with a guy named Chris. suddenly WI started experimenting and at the same time they shuffled Shiv up and down the batting order, guess they were not serious about his talent so lets hope that Chatters doesnt have the same experience as they try to revive Smith and others careers!""

dismissalText.commentary: Thilan Thushara run out (Taylor) 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Chaotic end! Two direct hits! The batsman missed a full delivery but ran for the bye. Ramdin's throw missed the stumps, Taylor picked it up, turned around and broke  the stumps at the non-striker's end. They run for the rebound. Another direct hit, from Ramdin, comes at the striker's end. Taufel takes the safe route and goes to the third umpire who rules that Taylor's throw had caught the batsman short. Phew!. So no run off the final ball.
